Source: le-vibe-ide
Section: editors
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Le Vibe Maintainers <maintainers@example.invalid>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13)
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no

Package: le-vibe-ide
Architecture: amd64
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}
Recommends: hicolor-icon-theme
Description: Lé Vibe IDE — Code OSS desktop shell (VSCode-linux tree)
 Installs a built VSCode-linux-* directory from editor/vscodium under
 /usr/lib/le-vibe/ide/ and exposes /usr/lib/le-vibe/bin/codium for the
 le-vibe stack launcher (PRODUCT_SPEC §7.3 — internal path; public CLI is lvibe).
 Also ships a Freedesktop menu entry (le-vibe.desktop) and hicolor icon so the
 app appears in the desktop environment alongside the stack package.
 .
 In-app auto-updates via a Lé Vibe-hosted channel are deferred to roadmap
 (PRODUCT_SPEC §7.3); use apt/releases or rebuild from source for upgrades.
 .
 Build: run dev/build.sh, then packaging/scripts/stage-le-vibe-ide-deb.sh and
 dpkg-buildpackage from packaging/debian-le-vibe-ide/ — see README.md there.
